claim.claim-text:
11. A handle assembly for a teeth cleaning system that includes a tray assembly, the handle assembly comprising:
a casing with an opening defined therein;
a shaft that extends through the opening in the casing, such that a first end of the shaft is external to the casing and engageable with the tray assembly;
a motor with a drive shaft that rotates during operation; and
a cam to which a second end of the shaft is coupled,
wherein the cam is configured to drive the shaft in a lateral direction in response to being rotated by the drive shaft of the motor.
